## Introduction
Many tools have been developed for *de novo* transposable element (TE) identification. But manual 
curation is still required for high quality TE annotation by experts. TE Trimmer is designed to replace and assistant
TE manual curation. 
![image](https://private-user-images.githubusercontent.com/75024559/278702015-5f01f336-f9bd-4827-89e4-7b1b055b7e3f.png?jwt=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..pdVoWAxEymwxSfrFfZwlIw1mDvD7GQ5sgjL2Ya-xGWs)

# Example of running TE Trimmer
```
python ./path_to_TE_Trimmer_folder/bin/main.py --input_file [your_TE_consensus_file_path] \
                                               --genome_file [your_genome_file_path] \
                                               --output_dir [output_directory]
```
